A cooldown timer is a mechanism that prevents an action from being performed too frequently within a certain time frame. Here's an example implementation in Markdown format:

### Cooldown Class

```markdown
### Cooldown Class
#### Properties
* `time`: The cooldown duration in seconds
* `lastUse`: The timestamp of the last time the cooldown was triggered

#### Methods
* `init(time)`: Initializes the cooldown with the specified duration
* `isReady()`: Checks if the cooldown is ready to be triggered
* `trigger()`: Triggers the cooldown and updates the last use timestamp
```

### Cooldown Implementation

```markdown
### Cooldown Implementation
#### Code
```javascript
class Cooldown {
  constructor(time) {
    this.time = time;
    this.lastUse = 0;
  }

  init() {
    this.lastUse = 0;
  }

  isReady() {
    const currentTime = Date.now();
    return currentTime - this.lastUse >= this.time * 1000;
  }

  trigger() {
    this.lastUse = Date.now();
  }
}
```

